 -- Function: ax_plot2d (EXPR, [VAR, MIN, MAX])
     Plot one or more expressions as interactive Plotly.js charts.  This
     is a convenience wrapper around ‘ax_draw2d’ that automatically
     creates ‘explicit()’ objects from expressions.

     Calling forms:

        • ‘ax_plot2d(expr, [var, min, max], options)’ -- single
          expression
        • ‘ax_plot2d([expr_1, ..., expr_n], [var, min, max], options)’
          -- multiple expressions

* Menu:

     * Examples::
     * Style Options::
     * Layout Options::


File: ax-plots.info,  Node: Examples,  Up: Definitions for ax-plots

1.2.1 Examples
--------------

/* Single expression */
ax_plot2d(sin(x), [x, -%pi, %pi])$

/* Multiple expressions */
ax_plot2d([sin(x), cos(x)], [x, -5, 5])$

/* With options */
ax_plot2d(x^2, [x, -3, 3], title="Parabola", color="red")$

