 -- Function: ax_polar (EXPR, [VAR, MIN, MAX])
     Plot r(θ) curves in polar coordinates as interactive Plotly.js
     charts.  Standalone function (like ‘ax_plot2d’).

     Calling forms:

        • ‘ax_polar(expr, [θ, min, max], options)’ -- single expression
        • ‘ax_polar([expr_1, ..., expr_n], [θ, min, max], options)’ --
          multiple expressions

* Menu:

     * Examples: Examples 4.
     * Style Options: Style Options 4.
     * Layout Options: Layout Options 4.


File: ax-plots.info,  Node: Examples 4,  Next: Style Options 4,  Prev: Layout Options 3,  Up: Examples

1.2.1.11 Examples
.................

/* Cardioid */
ax_polar(1 + cos(θ), [θ, 0, 2*%pi])$

/* Rose curve */
ax_polar(sin(3*θ), [θ, 0, 2*%pi], color="red", title="Rose Curve")$

/* Multiple curves */
ax_polar(
  [1 + cos(θ), 1 - cos(θ)],
  [θ, 0, 2*%pi],
  title="Cardioids"
)$

/* Spiral */
ax_polar(θ/10, [θ, 0, 6*%pi], title="Archimedean Spiral")$


