 -- Function: ax_vector_field (FX, FY, XVAR, XLO, XHI, YVAR, YLO, YHI)
     2D vector field (quiver) plot.  Use inside ‘ax_draw2d’.  Given a
     vector field F = (Fx(x,y), Fy(x,y)), samples on a grid and renders
     arrows showing the field direction and magnitude.

* Menu:

